INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (238,1,'2013-05-23 14:44:31','2013-05-23 18:44:31','<p class=\"p1\">That depends. First, if you&rsquo;ve just about depleted the battery, it may need to charge for up to twenty minutes before you can even turn it on. Next, it depends on how much usage you&rsquo;re talking about (a quick look at something, accessing a network, full-screen brightness web browsing?) and how much charging you&rsquo;re doing (low- or high-wattage adapter, USB port on your computer?).</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>iPad:</strong> The iPad&rsquo;s larger battery, and greater power consumption when in use, means that the things that generally drain an iDevice&rsquo;s battery (<span class=\"s1\"><strong>See <em>H</em></strong></span><strong><em>ow do I make my battery last longer? b</em>elow</strong>) can slurp out almost as much juice as you&rsquo;re putting in&mdash;sometimes, even <em>more</em>&mdash;if you&rsquo;re charging from a computer. This is especially true of the iPad 3 and 4, whose retina screens are power-hungry. If you must use your iPad but you also need to charge it from your computer, keep the brightness down, and network usage to a minimum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>iPhone/Touch:</strong> The iPhone/Touch is much less demanding when it comes to power, so you&rsquo;ll be able to charge it and use it at the same time, although heavy use can add to the charge time.</p>','Can I use my iDevice while it\'s charging?','','inherit','open','open','','153-revision-3','','','2013-05-23 14:44:31','2013-05-23 18:44:31','',153,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=238',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (239,1,'2013-05-21 18:28:29','2013-05-21 22:28:29','<p class=\"p1\">There are so many variables, there&rsquo;s no set answer. The fastest way to charge your iDevice is by turning it off&mdash;or at least putting it to sleep&mdash;and plugging it into an outlet using the power adapter and cable. This can recharge an iPad in 6-7 hours, and an iPhone/Touch in just a couple of hours. Using the iDevice while it&rsquo;s charging, or charging it through a computer connection, adds to the charge time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><em>Warning!</em></strong><em> The adapter you use affects the charging time. If you have multiple devices and adapters, using a higher-wattage adapter (the &ldquo;bricks&rdquo; are interchangeable) shortens charging time somewhat. The iPad 4 has a 12-watt adapter; earlier iPads, 10 and 12 watts; iPhone/Touch and iPad Mini, 5 watts.</em></p>','How long does it take to charge my iDevice?','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-2','','','2013-05-21 18:28:29','2013-05-21 22:28:29','',151,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=239',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (240,1,'2013-05-21 18:26:58','2013-05-21 22:26:58','<p class=\"p1\">It depends. USB ports don&rsquo;t provide a charge if the computer is off or sleeping, so you&rsquo;d have to leave it on. A port in a standalone display that&rsquo;s left on (even if it&rsquo;s sleeping) will likely work, as would a powered USB hub. Check by connecting your iDevice and seeing if the battery icon in the status bar shows it&rsquo;s charging.</p>','Can I charge my iDevice overnight by leaving it attached to my computer?','','inherit','open','open','','149-revision-2','','','2013-05-21 18:26:58','2013-05-21 22:26:58','',149,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=240',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (241,1,'2013-05-21 18:22:11','2013-05-21 22:22:11','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Use a power outlet:</strong> Use the power adapter and the cable that came with your iDevice. You can connect the dock end of the cable to a dock or directly to the device.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Use a computer:</strong> Use the cable and connect your iDevice to a USB 2.0 or 3.0 port. The ports on older computers, most keyboards, and USB hubs (unless they&rsquo;re separately powered) don&rsquo;t provide enough juice to charge your iDevice.</p>','How do I charge the battery?','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-2','','','2013-05-21 18:22:11','2013-05-21 22:22:11','',145,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=241',0,'revision','',0);
