INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (325,1,'2013-05-23 19:25:13','2013-05-23 23:25:13','<p class=\"p1\">If it&rsquo;s a desktop Mac, first check if the mouse or keyboard got disconnected. If you&rsquo;re using a wireless keyboard or mouse, the batteries may have died or your Bluetooth may be off. We like to check that the caps lock key lights up when we press it. If that works, then your keyboard is working; perhaps your mouse has a bad connection. Sometimes just unplugging and re-plugging the mouse will cause the Mac to &ldquo;wake up.&rdquo; If you&rsquo;re sure your mouse and keyboard are working, then you can force the application that froze to quit.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Pressing Command-Option-Escape will let you force quit any application (the one that froze). You&rsquo;ll see a window that lets you select which application to quit. When you force an application to quit, you lose all unsaved work in that application, but other open applications remain open and usable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">If these suggestions don&rsquo;t work, you may have lost all your work since you last saved. Restart by holding down the power button for a few seconds or press these three buttons together: Command-Control-Power Button.</p>','My Mac froze up. Now what?','','publish','open','open','','my-mac-froze-up-now-what','','','2013-05-28 14:33:30','2013-05-28 18:33:30','',0,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=325',55,'post','',0);
